In 2021 i was quickly becoming one of the top resin artists and had almost 42k followers, and then something wonderful happened and i got engaged to my best friend. So i put everything on hood and decided to focus on planning our wedding. While i was planning our wedding o quickly realized my heart was not in being a resin artist, and that i originally got into it for all the wrong reasons. While i have always had a creative side, i knew being a resin artist isn’t the outlet i wanted. Once we were married and i was able to focus on what i really wanted to do, i watched my follower count decline. And this morning i finally dropped below 40k. But honestly, it’s ok!! I just want to make our builder grade home into our custom dream home. And if you’re tagging along, than i am so grateful for you! Stay tuned because i am just getting started!!
.

1/2 C peanut butter
1/3 C Chocolate Protein Powder

3 Tbs honey
3 tsp water
Cinnamon to taste (optional)

This can’t be real. This can’t be happening. I’m just waiting to wake up from this nightmare. Everything was fine until it wasn’t. Last night i had to say goodbye to my sweet, kind, loving and loyal Nala. She has been my best friend for 10.5 years. How am i suppose to go through life without you? Last night we were snuggling on the couch by the fire like we always do, and then an hour later you were gone. I am broken. Completely, truly, and utterly broken. I feel as though my heart has been ripped out of my chest. I know you are no longer in pain, i know you’re running in heaven with Honey, Duke, Yokie, and Bella. And i know it is selfish of me to want you back instead of the peace you are finally in. I know God has wrapped you in his loving arms and you will be waiting for me when it is my time. 

If a dog could be a soulmate, you were absolutely mine. I’ll never have another dog like you, i know you were one of a kind. Everyone that ever met you fell instantly in love. It’s cliche, but we rescued each other. You brought SO much joy into my life, and our little family will never be the same without you. Cedar misses you, you were his rock. Matt misses you, you showed him the love of a Dane when he needed it the most. And even Ginger misses you, even though y’all only had 2 short weeks together.

I haven’t slept yet since you left me, i haven’t stopped crying. Nala, i don’t know if this house will ever feel like a home again without you in it.

Rest in Peace sweet Nala girl, I’ll make sure Cedar continues to run off the cows when they get too close to the fence. I love you more than words can describe, and i honestly don’t think my heart can ever fully recover from losing you..

Nala 10/27/11 - 4/10/23

To the cast and crew of the show, what you do for the families, and how flipping hard y’all work for them is something you should be proud of! All of you worked SO incredibly hard! All of you were so nice and patient with us. And i can’t thank ALL OF YOU enough for letting us be apart of it all!
